4:
...And that concludes today's class.
I'll see all of you again first thing
tomorrow.
6:
Looks like Professor Leleni isn't here
today either. I wonder what's going
on?
8:
I know why! She's out on official
Guild business in the woods!
10:
Hey, I've got an idea! How about we
give the professor a hand? That'll
surprise her for sure!
13:
We're finally done! That means I can
see my students again, starting
tomorrow!
16:
That's great! I'm sure they've missed
you a lot.
21:
I doubt it! They've probably been
enjoying the freedom—you take
your eyes off them for ONE minute
and they go wild!
25:
...Speaking from experience, I can
confirm that.
28:
Right?! They're always goofing off,
and they never pay attention!
32:
They don't take me seriously,
either—always poking fun and
disrespecting my authority!
37:
Well, anyway... Should we go report
our progress?
43:
...Did something happen? There
seems to be a lot of commotion.
46:
A group of brats got lost
somewhere. We're forming a search
party as we speak.
48:
Looks like they were students from
the academy... Apparently they
were looking for their teacher?
Professor "Leni", or something.
55:
D-descend from the clouds, g-great
thunderbolt! Take down our
enemies!
57: I-it's no good... It's too strong!
59:
D-don't take your eyes off of it!
That's what Professor Leleni always
said! It'll attack if we turn our backs!
65:
Don't you DARE lay a single finger on
any of my students!
69:
I call upon the skies—strike down,
glorious thunder!
72: It's gone! Professor Leleni saved us!
79:
Why are you all out here by
yourselves?! Don't you know how
dangerous this is?!
83: W-we just wanted to help you...
84: You... seemed so busy lately, so...
87:
R-really? You were all thinking
about... me?
91:
Still, that doesn't mean you can go
running off into danger like that.
93:
It's important to understand that
though you may wield great
magical powers, you are still a small
and fragile mortal being!
95:
Not being aware of your own
weaknesses can put you in grave
danger! Are we clear on that?
99: Is that so? Good. That settles it then.
102:
Quite the scary experience that was,
huh? Luckily your brave teacher
came to the rescue!
104: I apologize for being absent recently.
110:
Alright, alright! Take a number! I'm
not sure I can handle this affection
all at once!
113:
I call upon the skies—strike down,
glorious thunder!
115:
Wow! I did it! I did it! Professor, did
you see that?!
118:
Now isn't that a sight to behold.
Looks like they're finally paying
attention to what you have to say.
121:
Well... I AM happy that they've grown
more obedient, but...
124:
Voluntas is an academic institution,
not a place to train adventurers
looking to explore the Kaleidoscope!
We shouldn't only be teaching them
how to fight!
127: Me! Me! Me! I'll go next!
130:
...Ugh. What am I going to tell their
parents?
